 effects of back-diffusion on grain-surface reaction rates.\nBack-diffusion reduces reaction rates by a maximum factor of around 5 for the\ncanonical grain of $\\sim$10$^6$ surface sites, but this falls to unity at close\nto full surface coverage.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Apr 2017 16:17:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-05-24"}
